    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="178"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d178">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hart</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 115.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor herewith to inclose copy of a
                    note sent yesterday to the Colombian foreign office in the matter of the Star
                    and Herald.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. Burdett Hart.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hart</persName> to Mr. <persName
                                type="to">Paul</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of America.</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-24">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1898</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The circumstances of the case compel me to
                        recall to your excellency’s attention my note of October 6, in the matter of
                        the Panama Star and Herald claim, and to ask that your excellency favor me
                        with a definite reply thereto, in order that I may cable the same to my
                        Government on or before Wednesday the 26th instant, it being the desire of
                        my Government to close this incident without further delay.</p>
                    <p>I improve this opportunity to renew, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. Burdett Hart.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
